# Frontend (Next.js SPA)

## Structure

- Single page → `AppShell` client router (hash-based master views)
- Master views: Auth (login/register subviews), Playground, Monitoring
- `lib/webllm.ts` — browser-only; dynamic import `@mlc-ai/web-llm`
- `lib/api.ts` — typed client; refresh-on-401; tokens in localStorage (capstone tradeoff)

## Rules

- Never import WebLLM in server components / SSR paths
- Require WebGPU check before load; show clear fallback UX
- After generate: `POST /llm/runs` then show Deci.Scoring breakdown
- Env: `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` only (no secrets in the client)

## UI

Keep the monitoring/playground surface clear and dense — telemetry and scores first.
Avoid decorative card clutter that hides latency/tokens/grade.
